net.dean.jraw.models

Class Thing

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.dean.jraw.models.JsonModel
      • net.dean.jraw.models.RedditObject
        • net.dean.jraw.models.Thing
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    Account, Award, Contribution, LiveUpdate, ModAction, MoreChildren, MultiHubPaginator.MultiRedditId, MultiReddit, Subreddit, UserRecord

    @Model(kind=ABSTRACT)
public abstract class Thing
extends RedditObject
    The Thing class is the base class for most data structures returned by the Reddit API. Every Thing has an ID and a fullname (referred to as an ID36 in the Reddit source code). To construct a fullname, simply prepend tX_, where X is an integer. For a valid list of these prefixes, see here. However, this is not the same for all classes. The Account class's fullname will return the username instead of t2_<id>.
